div.ab:


The household of Qirṭās [...] ʿImrān the porter:


| thirty dirhams.


The household of Yūsuf al-Damanhūrī the carpenter: ten [dirhams].


ʿAṭā: ten [dirhams]. Thābit: ten [dirhams].


The money order for the received goods - flour included - totals seventy-three and a half [dirhams].


Chickpeas: half [dirham]; onions: one dirham; lemon: two dirhams;


carrots: one and a quarter dirhams; milk: three and a quarter [dirhams];


butter: half [dirham];


chicken eggs and other items: two and a half and a quarter dirhams. 


Of the [amount mentioned] above, seventy dirhams have been paid.
